      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Paradigm shift to what, if it goes off of the basic fundamentals of the current HoT-line the imbalance is negated by the fact that HoTs, Direct Heal and CH are already calculated into the paradigm. The fundamentals are there and it's already balanced against current content. People already use HoTs to heal in current&amp;nbsp;content, expanding their efficiency (meaning when to tick and when not to tick) how does it become unbalanced if it follows the current trend and limits that a direct heal or a Ch couldn't already accomplish? DoT's already gain 100% efficiency, why can't HoT's?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Healing mechanics haven't really been shaken up since the introduction of the DVA3/CR combo, I think we're over due for something new. &lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
