      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I have mixed feelings about reactive healing. In EQ2 it became just about the ONLY way that anyone used - it was basically overpowered. While I played EQ2 I did not even have any normal heal spells memmed 99% of the time.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;On the other hand, I could see a place for a limited reactive&amp;nbsp;heal - perhaps something like a weapon proc that would heal for a fairly large amount, but only go off maybe 3 times, and not every time. Basically it would be like a randomly triggered heal.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;But I am not too sure even about that, I can see some problems with any reactive heal that really does much. To be of any use, it would have to heal for a fairly large amount. But that same thing could make some raid encounters trivial.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
